Text.Value: Nothin' amiss.
Don't like strangers here, but...
Caught 'em sniffin' around. Easy marks - had the stench of the top-lands.
Did you notice your spiders ran off?
Go ahead - try me, ya shit!
Where did the drow come from?
No fight in 'em after that. Didn't so much as groan when I snapped their spines.
Quit distractin' me.
We get into a scrap, I bet they'll run off into the dark. Wastes of space.
Gods, that's horrific. I'll have your head!
Did you notice one of your spiders killed the other?
Let me see your eyes, underelf. Mm.
Red-eyed bastard! Eh... wait a second.
Nah - the spiders had already tired them out by the time Nere got his hands on them. Once he broke their brains, their tongues wouldn't stop waggin'.
Me - who else? My spiders sussed 'em out of hiding, then Nere taught 'em a thing or two, and I let 'em fly.
Shouldn't have hesitated, greyling. You'll be a fine sacrifice.
Hung them here as a warning. Ain't no one drughs with Clan Flameshade.

EditorData.NodeContext: Drugh = DROOG. Like GOOD, not FOOD. Expletive = 'fucks'

Text.Value: Who hung these drow out to dry?
Tell me the drow put up a fight, at least.

EditorData.logicalname: SELDARINE DROW - after asking about drow

Text.Value: She was the best at finding hide-aways under all this rubble. The other three combined had half as much brains.
Leave.
Eh? Oh, those worthless bugs. Always were the stupidest ones I ever raised. Hope the minotaurs get 'em.
Nere's dead. You want a medal, or a chest to pin it on?
I'll gut you, spiderspawn!
Absolute must'a took you in.
Eh? Blood-thirsty idiots! Who'd they go after? Xanta? Damn it!

Synopsis:
Drow hang from the bridge. PAD as we see them - “Duergar rarely stand up to drow so boldly.”
One duergar is here, patrolling with a crossbow. He tells us he’s keeping watch over the lake - these drow were trying to infiltrate the settlement, and more may come.
